author: The Telegraph
title: Win top Rugby World Cup 2015 tickets
text: Have you long since given up on getting tickets to see Rugby World Cup 2015 matches? Maybe you were unlucky in the ballot, or were simply too late to apply in the first place. Well, if that is the case, you are in luck. Courtesy of Toshiba, official sponsor of this year’s competition, there are free tickets to six Rugby World Cup 2015 matches to give away. Enter the free prize draw below and you could win one of… • Two pairs of tickets for England v Fiji 8pm, 18 September, at Twickenham Stadium • Two pairs of tickets for Wales v Uruguay 2.30pm, 20 September, at Millennium Stadium • One pair of tickets for England v Wales 8pm, 26 September, at Twickenham Stadium • Two pairs of tickets for England v Uruguay 8pm, 10 October, at Manchester City Stadium • One pair of tickets for the first quarter-final 4pm, 17 October, at Twickenham Stadium • Two pairs of tickets for the first semi-final 4pm, 24 October, at Twickenham Stadium Online Form - Win top Rugby World Cup 2015 tickets telegraph.co.uk Follow @telegraph
